  Locus:
    Page: 271
    Verse: 16
Tags:
  - Immortality/Eternity
---
Eternity has no gray hairs. The flowers fade, the heart withers, man grows
old and dies, the world lies down in the sepulchre of ages, but time writes
no wrinkles on the brow of eternity.
